The methoxy group (OC) is an electron-donating group which can increase the melting point due to an increase in intermolecular interactions like hydrogen bonding, raising the melting point by approximately +12 °C. Collectively considering the effects of these functional groups, we add their individual contributions to the basic aromatic ring to predict the melting point.
